<item>
            <title>[SPARK-5681] Calling graceful stop() immediately after start() on StreamingContext should not get stuck indefinitely</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5681</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes the receiver will be registered into tracker after ssc.stop is called. Especially when stop() is called immediately after start(). So the receiver doesn&apos;t get the StopReceiver message from the tracker. In this case, when you call stop() in graceful mode, stop() would get stuck indefinitely.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
